17/02/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Ion Iliescu, the honourary president of the Social Democratic Party (PSD), withdrew from all posts in the party Tuesday (February 16th). Iliescu, 80, has had a long political career, starting with the former communist party. He served as Romania's president for two terms before quitting all official posts while wielding vast influence over the PSD. (Gandul, Adevarul, Ziare - 17/02/10; Mediafax, Realitatea, Hotnews.ro - 16/02/10)
